<HEADLINE>
HOW ABOUT CSUN-UCLA IN 2002 OPENER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JILL PAINTER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ UCLA is looking for an opponent for the 2002
football season opener. If Cal State Northridge coach Jeff Kearin
had his way, the search would be over. CSUN plays at least one
Division I-A team every year and Kearin wouldn't mind traveling
down the road to the Rose Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   Kearin said he talks to every Division I-A coach or athletic
director he meets about the prospect of getting on their schedule.
Kearin said he talked to Bob Toledo about a game against UCLA at a
golf tournament last summer.
</P>
<P>
   ``He said it would be a hard sell for their fans and alumni to
play a I-AA,'' Kearin said. ``. . . I'd love to play UCLA. We'd bus
over, it would be a big payday and it's a local game. It would be
one of the greatest experiences this program has ever had. But I
just don't know if they'd be open to that.''
</P>
<P>
   But that was then and UCLA still hasn't filled that slot. Every
Thursday, the Northridge coach makes calls to try to land a
Division I-A opponent. Kearin might call Toledo today to let him
know CSUN is still available.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Toldeo) has been a small-college coach and he knows the
trials and tribulations of being a small-college program,'' Kearin
said. ``It would be a huge value to us emotionally, financially and
for our stature.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Very special teams: This is the one area in which the
Matadors have consistently played well this year. CSUN will be
challenged when CSUN hosts Idaho State in a key Big Sky Conference
game Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   DeRonn Finley returned a punt 85 yards for a touchdown in ISU's
41-39 win over Sacramento State.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're solid enough to contain a good special team from
anybody,'' Kearin said. ``Fortunately, we have a good punter who
puts the ball up high. But our punt coverage hasn't been that great
and that's my job.
</P>
<P>
   ``Finley is a threat every time he touches the ball. But I feel
good about our special teams now. We blocked a punt last week and
that always helps.''
</P>
<P>
   CSUN's Ethan Beck is second in the Big Sky in punting with a
43.6-yard average over 18 punts _ including four inside the 20.
Finley averages 15.2 yards per punt return and also has 11 catches
for 159 yards and one touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   __ Injury report: A day after running routes, wide receiver Drew
Amerson's right knee was OK. Amerson, who hyperextended his knee,
is day to day. . . . Defensive lineman Erik Gardner sat out
Tuesday's practice because of a bad back but practiced Wednesday. .
. . Defensive lineman Andy Zaldivar (ankle) is practicing in full
pads. . . . Receiver D.J. Hackett, who suffered a minor knee injury
against Northern Arizona, is OK and will play Saturday. . . .
Receiver Jamaal Perry is nursing an ankle injury but is expected to
play Saturday.
</P>
</TEXT>
