</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONGO-QUAGMIRE-UN-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DONGO, THE CONGO _ His name was Kabwanga Makengo. Born
Lubumbashi, June 3, 1980. Private, 2nd Brigade of the army of the
Democratic Republic of Congo. Catholic. Unmarried. The photograph
shows a baby face startled by the camera. Makengo's muddied _ or
bloodied _ identity card lay in the trench where he is buried, next
to a smashed anti-aircraft gun. When the rebels of the Movement for
the Liberation of Congo (MLC) took this tiny trading post on the
Ubangi River on Sept. 7, they put the 34 dead government soldiers
in the trenches and covered them over. Suddenly, this war has
turned serious. &QL;
</P>
