</P>
<P>
   &UR; WILL CONSUMERS TREAD MORE CAREFULLY AS SUV WOES ACCELERATE? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SUV-WOES-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DETROIT _ Depending on how you look at them, SUVs are either
menace or salvation. Despite their propensity to roll over more
frequently than other vehicles, a passenger is more likely to
survive a crash in an SUV than in a smaller sedan. That has led
millions of Americans to trade their cars in for off-roaders in
recent years. But it is also prompting officials with the National
Highway Traffic Safety Administration to consider tougher
regulations on SUVs. &QL;
</P>
