<P>
   TV-OLYMPICS (Undated) _ the biggest problem with this year's
Olympics coverage hasn't been what NBC has televised. No, the
biggest setback for NBC has been what the other networks, and cable
outlets, and Internet sites, haven't shown. And that's still NBC's
fault, since it isn't sharing television footage with other
networks _ or even its own affiliates _ until it's too old to be
news. By MARK McGUIRE.
