   FOOD (``d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HASH-BROWNS (Albany, N.Y.) _ Hash browns do not have to come
from the frozen food section, nor do they have to be time-consuming
to make. Hash browns, those wonderful breakfast potatoes, can be
made quite easily from a few leftover potatoes. By RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
<P>
   CARMELIZATION (Albany, N.Y.) _ Caramelization is a rather
complex process in which sugar melts when heated to 315 degrees and
the resulting molecules, if heated more, react with each other to
make different sugars that happen to be brown. But skip the
chemistry lesson and remember two things: Caramelization occurs at
very high temperatures (325 degrees) and it progresses very
quickly. By RUTH FANTASIA
</P>
