<P>
   SKATEBOARD-PRO (Undated) _ At 32, Tony Hawk could be considered
the elder statesman of skateboarding. Just don't tell the skating
legend to give up his board for an adult job. ``I feel like there's
always been a stigma attached to skating that it's just for kids,''
Hawk says from his home in Carlsbad, Calif. Now the ``Michael
Jordan of skateboarding'' is soaring to new heights _ with a
world-touring exhibitions and a new book. By RENE A. GUZMAN.
</P>
