   RAC-RACETRACKS-PROBE (Saratoga Springs, N.Y.) _ A state attorney
general's investigation into Saratoga Race Course and the state's
two other thoroughbred racetracks run by the New York Racing
Association is focusing on mutuel clerks who may have knowingly
laundered money for organized crime, a source close to the
investigation said. By DENNIS YUSKO.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-GREEK-VICTORY (Sydney, Australia) _ For the first time in,
oh, 2,000 years or so, a Greek athlete has won a gold medal at 200
meters in the Olympic Games. Back then, the Greeks staged an
Olympic Games that are considered Ancient today. But never in the
history of the Modern Olympics has a Greek athlete won a gold medal
in the 200-meter dash. Or any medal, for that matter. By JOHN
CRUMPACKER.
</P>
<P>
