   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ LUFKIN, Texas _ We all know people like
that. You know, those whose elevator doesn't go all the way to the
top floor. The ones who are fry or two short of a Happy Meal. Folks
whose motor is running but they can't get it out of Park. When it
comes to the colloquial put-down, we take to it like, well, a hog
to slop. I received an e-mail the other day that purports to be
``actual employee performance evaluations in a large U.S.
corporation.'' More than likely, the list is from the imagination
of someone with too much time on his hands, but they do have a ring
of truth that is all too familiar: (Ernest Murray is managing
editor of The Lufkin Daily News) EDS: Embargoed for Sunday. MOVED
</P>
