<P>
   INDONESIA-SUHARTO (Jakarta) _ An Indonesian court dismissed all
charges against Indonesia's former leader Suharto and abandoned his
landmark corruption trial after doctors found him too sick to face
charges. One Suharto supporter died as hundreds of Suharto
opponents took to the streets. By Calvin Sims.
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-ELECTIONS (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ The opposition
threatened a general strike that would shut down schools, offices
and all institutions until Slobodan Milosevic recognizes its
election victory. By Steven Erlanger.
