   ISRAEL-UNREST (Jerusalem) _ Israel's opposition leader, Ariel
Sharon, on Thursday visited Temple Mount, a shrine that is at the
center of peace talks, and clashes immediately broke out, with riot
police firing rubber bullets at 200 Palestinians. By Joel
Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   DENMARK-EURO (Copenhagen) _ Exit polls from Thursday's vote
showed that the Danes were moving toward rejecting the euro. By
Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   PERU-POLITICS (Washington) _ President Alberto Fujimori of Peru
arrived in Washington Thursday for meetings with officials from the
Organization for American states and requested to meet with
``high-level'' U.S. officials. (Byline to come)
</P>
<P>
   LOCKERBIE-TRIAL (Camp Zeist, the Netherlands) _ The defense
continued dismantling the testimony of the prosecution's star
witness in the trial on the bombing of PanAm Flight 103. By Donald
G. McNeil Jr.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-BRIEFS (Undated) _ World news in brief.
