<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Hard to believe, but the chief justice of the
United States, of all people, is pushing to return bribery to the
federal judicial system. No less than William H. Rehnquist himself
is asking Congress to scrap the 1989 ban on honoraria for Supreme
Court justices and most other federal jurists. And what is more, he
has support for this curious notion from some substantial part of
the GOP caucus. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for Cox
Newspapers.) MOVED THURSDAY.
