though rain is still playing hide-and-seek, meaning the
temperatures are tolerable, but the land is still ridiculously dry
even with a few showers. Forest fires are still a fact of life, and
anybody who is dumb enough to burn outdoors or chunk a cigarette
out a car window ought to be horsewhipped.(Gary Borders is editor
and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel.) EDS: EMBARGOED
for Sunday. MOVED.
