<SLUG> BC-BREAST-CANCER-RUN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT; 
RUN FOR YOUR LIFE 

</HEADLINE>
bc-BREAST-CANCER
cc,78p3  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
EDS: SIDEBAR BELOW 
By BARBARA DEWITT 
c. 2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   In between flea markets and football games, the Rose Bowl in
Pasadena has set Oct. 15 aside for the fifth annual Susan G. Komen
Breast Cancer Foundation's Race for the Cure. The 5K run/fitness
walk event is sponsored by JC Penney stores and begins at 8:30 a.m.
The Komen Race for the Cure was founded in 1982 and is held
annually in 95 cities across the country so there's a bit of
competition. Los Angeles raised $800,000 last year. For more
information, call (626) 577-2700.
</P>
<P>
   In the news less than breast cancer, but expected to kill
187,000 people this year, is pancreatic cancer. On Sunday, 1,500
people are expected to run for this cause in the FILA City
Challenge 5K/10K Race and Kiddie 1K Run. The morning activities
will also include exercise warmups, entertainment and a sponsor
expo fair. Funds raised at the event will benefit the Ronald S.
Hirshberg Pancreatic Cancer Research Center at UCLA. The race
begins at 8:30 a.m. at Veterans Administration Grounds, 11000
Wilshire Blvd., Los Angeles. All participating children will
receive blue ribbons and T-shirts. For more information, call (310)
472-6310 or visit www.pancreatic.org. &QL; 
---ON THE RIGHT TRACK &QL; 
By Barbara Dominguez &QL; 
BMW is serious about its cars and serious about fighting breast
cancer.
</P>
<P>
   Aside from hosting a driving clinic for women, Germany's
!ital!uber!off! female-friendly automaker is sponsoring the
Ultimate Drive for the Susan G. Komen Breast Cancer Foundation, a
national ongoing event for breast cancer research, where
participants can test drive the vehicle of their choice -- from the
swift M3 line to the luxurious 7-series -- on a 10- to 12-mile
route. For every mile driven, BMW donates $1 to the foundation.
</P>
<P>
   With a goal of $1 million, drivers will need to log 1 million
miles -- so put the pedal to the metal.
</P>
<P>
   The traveling benefit makes various pit stops in the Southland
now through Oct. 17. To schedule a fund-raising test drive, visit
your local BMW dealership or call (877) 423-7483.
</P>
</TEXT>
