<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Season-ending shows left many hanging, so here's a recap
 &HT;    By Laura Dempsey
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It wouldn't be summer without a few television cliffhangers to
ponder. Here's a recap of our favorite open endings from last
season:
</P>
<P>
   _ Everybody Loves Raymond: Brother Robert has to choose between
his ex-wife and his girlfriend. CBS, Monday.
</P>
<P>
   _ Third Watch: Will Jimmy live? NBC, Monday.
</P>
<P>
   _ Judging Amy: Vincent was hurt in an explosion, but we don't
know to what extent. And it may be Amy's fault. CBS, Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ The West Wing: This is the second-biggest one: Who, exactly,
got shot? All we know is more than one person was hit. Find out who
and how serious the wounds are on NBC's two-hour season opener,
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Jamie Foxx Show: Jamie doesn't know whether to go on tour
with Nicole or stay home. If he stays home, he'll probably ask
Fancy to marry him. WB, Oct. 8.
</P>
<P>
   _ ER: Carol's gone and Carter's in rehab. On NBC, Oct. 12.
</P>
<P>
   _ Will &AMP; Grace: Has Will gone crazy? Fired and lovesick, he's
off on an island. Sounds sane to us. NBC, Oct. 12.
</P>
<P>
   _ Law &AMP; Order: Does Adam get voted out of office? Yes _ Steven
Hill is leaving the show, and Dianne Wiest is taking his place. On
NBC, Oct. 18.
</P>
<P>
   _ Law &AMP; Order: Special Victims Unit: Somebody's been deemed too
unstable to serve. OK, who? Find out Oct. 20 on NBC.
</P>
<P>
   _ Frasier: This is the big one. Who's it going to be, Daphne?
Last seen, she was leaving in an RV with Niles, with Donny stranded
at the altar. On NBC, Oct. 24.
</P>
<P>
   _ Malcolm in the Middle: Where's Dewey? He was last seen chasing
a red balloon to parts unknown. Find out where on Fox, Nov. 5.
</P>
<P>
   _ The X-Files: Mulder's off somewhere with aliens; Cigarette
Smoking Man may be dead; Scully's preggers. One mystery's sort of
solved _ Mulder will be back, if only for the 11 episodes left on
David Duchovny's contract. In his place, look for Robert Patrick.
For the rest of the truth, tune in to Fox, Nov. 5.
</P>
<P>
   _ NYPD Blue: Kirkendall is on the lam from Internal Affairs (and
actress Andrea Thompson won't be back, so that one's solved);
Sipowicz wonders if little Theo will be his next loved one to die
an untimely death. ABC, sometime in January.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
