A5233 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-FALLTV-NAMES29-COX     09-28 0164
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FALLTV-NAMES29-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eds: RUWhat's in a name?
 &HT;    By Laura Dempsey
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   JAG is not DAG, though both involve men in uniform. The Trouble
With Normal has nothing to do with Normal, Ohio _ in fact, it used
to be called People Who Fear People.
</P>
<P>
   Last season, a couple of show titles had us furrowing our brows
_ Now and Again was futuristic; Once and Again was here-and-now.
This season title confusion is everywhere, but swirls especially
around Dark Angel, a Buffy the Vampire Slayer-like series that has
nothing to do with Buffy or her hunky spinoff, plain old Angel. And
Touched by an Angel is even farther removed.
</P>
<P>
   What is in a name? Does The Geena Davis Show make any sense at
all, given that her character's name is Teddie? Cursed used to be
The Steven Weber Show, but does the name change help?
</P>
<P>
   Probably not. If it's good, we'll watch it.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
