<P>
   HIRING (EMOTIONALLY) SMART
</P>
<P>
   EMOTIONAL-INTELLIGENCE-HARVARD-NEWSLETTERS _ Nobody questions
the importance of emotional intelligence for leadership. Studies
indicate that your emotional intelligence or emotional quotient
(EQ) accounts for 15 percent to 45 percent of your success on the
job. (Your IQ, by comparison, is said to account for less than 6
percent.) But it's been difficult to apply the principles of
emotional intelligence to everyday situations. Now that's changing.
Companies have developed assessment tools that can be incorporated
into hiring, performance-appraisal and executive-development
processes. A report. By the editorial staff of Harvard Management
Update.
</P>
