   COMMUNICATION BREAKDOWN: EIGHT MISTAKES MANAGERS MAKE
</P>
<P>
   COMMUNICATION-BREAKDOWN-HARVARD-NEWSLETTERS _ How can management
communications be screwed up? Let us count the ways. Some can be
traced to the idiosyncrasies of leaders. But then there are the
common foul-ups that every company falls prey to at one time or
another. Here are eight typical blunders and how to avoid them. By
Steve Robbins. From the Harvard Management Communication Letter.
