   SACRED CHIMAYO &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHIMAYO, N.M. _ Pilgrims line up daily outside the Santuario de
Chimayo, carrying plastic baggies and a fervent wish to be healed.
For 200 years, the ground in Chimayo has been considered sacred,
and the tradition continues in this tiny village outside Santa Fe,
one of the places where you can still get a glimpse of
old-fashioned New Mexico. By PATRICIA RODRIGUEZ. Story has moved in
``t'' travel category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
