<P>
   CHENEY-PROFILE _ Troy, Mich. - No one is suggesting that Dick
Cheney is winning votes left and right with his stem-winding
oratory. The former Defense Secretary is so reserved that even when
he is on the attack, he peppers his remarks with ``if you will''
and ``it seems to me.'' The Cheney who is best at campaigning is
not Dick, but his wife, Lynne, who tries to humanize her husband
when she introduces him. (Sherman, The Altanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   LIEBPROFILE _ ORLANDO, Fla. _ C-Span's cameras are rolling,
causing Joseph Lieberman to, you should pardon the expression, ham
it up. ``Time after time, I tell myself that I'm so lucky to be
loved by you,'' Lieberman sings as he waits for another in a round
of television interviews via satellite. Kiki McLean, his press
secretary, interjects, ``You're on C-Span, sir.'' Lieberman is a
man who looks like he's having fun on the campaign trail,
sprinkling Yiddish into his talks, always making sure to remind
listeners of the economic growth of the past eight years. (Sherman,
The Altanta Journal-Constitution)
