   PILL-POLITICS (Washington) _ Approval of the sale of the
abortion pill RU-486 will have far-reaching social and political
repercussions. By Mary Leonard. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   RESEARCH-SAFETY (Undated) _ Federal research safety chief,
laying out his goals for the first time, says he will not back off
on enforcement but will focus on preventing harm to research
subjects by professionalizing the oversight system. By Alice
Dembner. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-INDICTMENT (Boston) _ Backed up by a stack of recently
unearthed bodies, federal prosecutors charge fugitive mobster
Whitey Bulger with murder for the first time. His sidekick, Stevie
Flemmi, is charged along with him in 10 of the 18 killings. The
indictment also names former FBI agent John Connolly, who used
Bulger and Flemmi as informants. By Shelley Murphy and Ralph
Ranalli. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-FBI (Boston) _ Bringing down the murderous Mafia was so
important that cutting deals with more benign gangsters like Bulger
and Flemmi was an unsavory necessity for the FBI. But who were the
really bad guys? By Ralph Ranalli. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   OIL-PRESSURE (Prague) _ As police clash with protesters, a
different kind of conflict is brewing at the IMF and World Bank
meetings _ a battle over the price of oil. By Brian Whitmore. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
