the one fate it never expected: a defeat. By John Powers. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   OLY-RYAN-COLUMN (Sydney) _ For Marion Jones there never was an
issue. The world could think whatever it wanted about her husband.
C.J. Hunter wasn't going to run that 200-meter race. She was. By
Bob Ryan. 990 words.
</P>
<P>
