<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ The number of hybrid-fuel vehicles
available to the public has just doubled.
</P>
<P>
   A hybrid is a vehicle that has more than one power source _ in
this case, a 44-horsepower electric motor and a 70-horsepower,
inline, four-cylinder gasoline motor. The newcomer, joining Honda's
Insight in the market place, is Toyota's Prius (pronounced pre-us).
(Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   THE-MECHANIC _ ATLANTA _ The question of whether to clean the
``self-cleaning'' Multec fuel injectors on a 1990 Camaro _ broached
by R.P Borsody last week _ prompted me to delve into an area for
which I thought I had a definitive answer. However, my research of
real-world conditions revealed, as is often the case, that the
factory information I have believed to be gospel contains some
discrepancies. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
