<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-28 18:13 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5489 &Cx1f; tad-z
u a BC-MORRIS-SIDE0929-COX     09-28 0488
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MORRIS-SIDE0929-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Morris offers inside glimpse of Clinton presidency
 &HT;    By David Brown
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   OXFORD, Ohio _ Dick Morris has known the president and first
lady for many years. He worked for Bill Clinton in the 1978, 1982,
1986 and 1990 governor's races in Arkansas and rejoined Clinton in
late 1994, after Republicans took control of Congress.
</P>
<P>
   Morris, at Miami University on Wednesday night for a lecture,
provided glimpses into the president's personal life and also spoke
at length about the upcoming presidential election and Hillary
Clinton's bid for a Senate seat from New York.
</P>
<P>
   Morris on Clinton's peccadilloes:
</P>
<P>
   ``He's had hundreds of women since he's been in the White House
. . . You (referring to the president's inner circle) had to be a
moron to believe this guy after his past record (with women).''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on the president's personal vs. public life:
</P>
<P>
   ``Which Bill do you want, the Saturday Night Bill or the Sunday
Morning Bill?''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on the impeachment:
</P>
<P>
   ``I support him being indicted when he leaves office. And I
think he'll be convicted of perjury and fined $10,000. I do not
feel he should have been removed from office.''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on the private Clinton:
</P>
<P>
   ``In private, he's a cold fish ... he projects empathy in public
but actually he's just reflecting things back ... he doesn't have
much love for anyone.''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on Bill and Hillary's relationship:
</P>
<P>
   ``Hillary loves Bill, and Bill loves Bill, so it works out ...
She gets things when he's caught cheating ... After Monica, she got
the Senate. Basically he subordinates the entire administration to
get her elected.''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on China-gate:
</P>
<P>
   ``Of all the Clinton scandals, the one he should have gotten
impeached over is taking money from Loral for giving away our
nuclear secrets to China.''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on his role in Clinton's 1996 re-election campaign:
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he's been a good president, and I'm proud I helped get
him re-elected. But I did not know in 1996 that he was doing all
this stuff.''
</P>
<P>
   Morris on Bush-Gore 2000:
</P>
<P>
   ``The American people basically like Bush more ... The problem
is, all of the issues that used to push the Republicans like crime
and welfare reform have gone away. So what do you need a Republican
for?''
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think it makes a lot of difference who wins - both are
good men, both are centrists, and both will lead their party in a
new direction.''
</P>
<P>
   On Hillary Clinton's Senate bid vs. Rick Lazio:
</P>
<P>
   ``If Hillary gets less than 50 percent of the vote in the final
poll before Election Day, she will lose. If the final polls show
Hillary defeating Lazio by 48-44, she will likely lose the election
by 52-48. Hillary has got to pull her poll number up to 50 percent
in order to win. Forty-eight percent won't be good enough.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
