<SLUG> BC-FBN-JERRY-RICE-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     TV CAMERAS MISS A BIG HUG 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By KEVIN LYNCH  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTA CLARA, Calif. _ Television cameras don't lie, but they
often fail to tell the whole story. Take the image of wide receiver
Jerry Rice bellowing at San Francisco 49ers coach Steve Mariucci
during Sunday's 41-24 49ers win in Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   What cameras didn't capture was Rice going up to Mariucci
shortly after his outburst and giving Mariucci a hug. Rice, who
appears embarrassed by the incident, refused to discuss the matter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now I'm focused on Arizona,'' Rice said of the 49ers'
opponent this weekend at Candlestick Park. ``I'm past all that.
It's ancient history.''
</P>
<P>
   But Mariucci thought television treatment of Rice was unfair.
``I guess I would prefer that it wouldn't end up on television like
it did, because they don't show the whole story,'' Mariucci said.
He also said Rice apologized right after his outburst and then
hugged his head coach.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Television) doesn't tell the accurate story either, you can
really get your imagination going,'' Mariucci said. ``It was a
little bit different than it was perceived, I think. I wish the
hugs and kisses would have been on television, too, because he
bounced back real fast.''
</P>
<P>
   It's not the first time Rice has exploded at Mariucci and then
apologized both in the media and to Mariucci. He did so in 1998,
during a Monday night 45-10 thrashing of the Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   ``Maybe he feels like he wants to be more productive towards the
win,'' Mariucci said. ``It was like a quick hurricane and then it
was over. I think he does it to get himself going.''
</P>
<P>
   The outburst began with Rice upset after dropping a wobbly pass
from Jeff Garcia. Rice, a noted perfectionist, was first angry with
Garcia and then turned on Mariucci when the coach asked what was
going on.
</P>
<P>
   Mariucci said Rice apologized repeatedly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
