   INDONESIA-SUHARTO (Jakarta, Indonesia) _ An Indonesian court
dismissed all charges against Suharto, the former president, and
abandoned his landmark corruption trial after doctors found him to
be too sick to face charges. One Suharto supporter died in riots as
hundreds of Suharto opponents took to the streets. These events
followed by one day the sentencing of Suharto's son, Tommy, to 18
months on corruption charges. By Calvin Sims.
