Organization of Oil Exporting Countries ended two days of meetings
here Thursday with a call for a ``constructive dialogue'' with the
main industrialized consumer nations in order to stabilize
skyrocketing oil prices, but said any such talks would also have to
address issues such as debt relief and gasoline taxes. By Larry
Rohter.
