<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEALTHINSURANCE-DATA-0929-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    By CHARLES W. HOLMES
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AMERICA'S UNINSURED
</P>
<P>
   TOTAL: 42.6 million uninsured in 1999, or 15.5 percent of the
U.S. population; 44.3 million uninsured in 1998, 16.3 percent of
the population; Change 1998-99: 1.7 million people, or -0.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
