premieres planned for his opening season, the Second Symphony by
John Corigliano in November and ``The Map,''' ``a multi-media
concerto for cello and orchestra'' in February. Neither score has
come in yet, which makes Ozawa a little nervous. But the
Corigliano, a 35-minute work for strings, harp and percussion is
reportedly complete. Ozawa during an interview earlier this week.
(John Bohn/The Boston Globe)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) MOUNT WASHINGTON, N.H. -- Sept. 28, 2000 --
AUTOS-COLUMN-BOS -- You may have seen the bumper stickers that
read, ``THIS CAR CLIMBED MOUNT WASHINGTON.'' To that, I say big
deal. They ought to read, ``THIS CAR GOT DOWN MOUNT WASHINGTON.''
That's because, with modern engines and better cooling systems,
overheating on the way up is not the threat it once was. Instead,
the dangers lurk in the descent, where the wrong transmission, bad
brakes, poor driving technique, or too heavy a load can lead to
dangerous runaways. An SUV descends Mt. Washington earlier this
month. (Jonathan Wiggs/The Boston Globe)
</P>
