``The Civil War'' and continued with ``Baseball.'' ``Jazz,'' a
10-night, 19-hour documentary is one of the most highly anticipated
programs of the new television season. It is filled with striking
concatenations of word, music and image. The documentary, which
took six years to complete will be broadcast on PBS beginning Jan.
8. Burns on the roof of a sound recording studio in New York. (Sara
Krulwich/The New York Times)
