that has taken up every inch of gallery space for the last year.
The show covers the years from 1960 to the present, which have
been, over all, a dynamite, don't-stop-running time for art. Yet in
presentation, the period looks surprisingly well-behaved. One of
the works on exhibit: ``African-American Flag'' (1990), by David
Hammons. (The Museum of Modern Art/The New York Times)
